data.enText: a person who pays rent for the use of a room, building, land, etc. to the person who owns it

data.chText: 他们赶走了未交房租的房客。
data.enText: They had evicted their tenants for non-payment of rent.

data.chText: 装修是一位前房客搞的。
data.enText: The decorating was done by a previous tenant.
tenant farmers (= ones who do not own their own farms)
to live or work in a place as a tenant

simple_means.memory_skill: ten 拿住 + ant 表人 → 拿〔钱〕租房之人 → 房客

tr: someone who pays rent to use land or a building or a car that is owned by someone else
example: the landlord can evict a tenant who doesn't pay the rent

tr: any occupant who dwells in a place
a holder of buildings or lands by any kind of title (as ownership or lease)

value.def: A tenant is someone who pays rent for the place they live in, or for land or buildings that they use.

example.ex: Regulations placed clear obligations on the landlord for the benefit of the tenant...
example.tran: 为维护房客的利益，条例明确规定了房东负有的各项义务。

example.ex: Landowners frequently left the management of their estates to tenant farmers.
example.tran: 地主们经常将土地的管理交给佃农。

trans: (房屋或公寓有合法权利的)现有房客，现租户
